entries.name: RootChainManager
entries.description: Main configuration contract to manage tokens, token types, escrows (predicates) for given token types. It also serves as an entry point for deposits and withdrawals effectively acting as a token router.

entries.name: StakeManagerExtension
entries.description: Contract primarily used to check whether a validator is whitelisted or not. It also provides the ability to update the validator registry address.

entries.name: StateSender
entries.description: Smart contract allowing whitelisted addresses to send messages to contracts on the child chain.

entries.name: StakingInfo
entries.description: Contains logging and getter functions about staking.

entries.name: ValidatorRegistry
entries.description: Defines the whitelist of validators that can stake and therefore participate in the PoS consensus protocol.

entries.name: WithdrawalManager
entries.description: Contract handling usersâ€™ withdrawal finalization for tokens escrowed in DepositManager.

entries.name: ExitNFT
entries.description: NFTs used to represent a withdrawal in the withdrawal PriorityQueue (Only used for tokens initially deposited via DepositManager).

receivedPermissions.description: can update the validator registry address used to check whitelist inclusion.
can update the whitelist of validators
can update the root chain it references.
can update how much of the slashed funds go to the proposer and reporter.

entries.name: DepositManager
entries.description: Contract to deposit and escrow ETH, ERC20 or ERC721 tokens.

entries.name: SlashingManager
entries.description: Contract that allows the consensus supermajority to slash validators.

entries.name: Governance
entries.description: Simple contract that allows the owner to call an `update` function on arbitrary contracts.

entries.name: RootChain
entries.description: Contract storing chain checkpoints. Note that validity of these checkpoints is not verified, it is assumed to be valid if signed by 2/3 of the validators.

entries.name: Registry
entries.description: Maintains the addresses of the contracts used in the system.
